dcMasterTc.name: dcMasterTc

revisions.description: DCL June 2013 files with Arris changes merged in

dcMasterTc.contactinfo: Postal: Data Connection Ltd. 100 Church Street Enfield Middlesex EN2 6BQ United Kingdom Tel: +44 20 83661177 E-mail: info@dataconnection.com
dcMasterTc.description: The set of common Textual Conventions for use in all DCL MIBs.

AdminStatus.name: AdminStatus
AdminStatus.description: The desired administrative state of a MIB row.

OperStatus.name: OperStatus
OperStatus.description: The current operational state of a MIB row. This set of values is used by many Data Connection products written before 2006.

BaseOperStatus.name: BaseOperStatus
BaseOperStatus.description: The current operational state of a MIB row. This is a complete set of values used by all Data Connection products.

NpgOperStatus.name: NpgOperStatus
NpgOperStatus.description: The current operational state of a MIB row. This set of values has been used by the Data Connection Networking Protocols Group since 2006.

NumericIndex.name: NumericIndex
NumericIndex.description: A numeric index value or identifier.

NumericIndexOrZero.name: NumericIndexOrZero
NumericIndexOrZero.description: Either a numeric index value or identifier, or the value zero with a special meaning defined by the object description. Do not use this TC for MIB table index objects. Zero is not valid for such objects.

EntityIndex.name: EntityIndex
EntityIndex.description: The HAF entity index value identifying a DC software entity. This TC is deprecated. Use NumericIndex for all indexes.

EntityIndexOrZero.name: EntityIndexOrZero
EntityIndexOrZero.description: The HAF entity index value identifying a DC software entity, or zero which is used to indicate that the entity is not present. This TC is deprecated. Use NumericIndexOrZero for all references to indexes.

AuthUserDataString.name: AuthUserDataString
AuthUserDataString.description: A string of user data that will be passed to the a0auth interface.

StdAccessListListIndex.name: StdAccessListListIndex
StdAccessListListIndex.description: An arbitrary index value identifying a standard access list.

StdAccessListListIndexOrZero.name: StdAccessListListIndexOrZero
StdAccessListListIndexOrZero.description: An arbitrary index value identifying a standard access list or zero for no access list.

StdAccessListRuleIndex.name: StdAccessListRuleIndex
StdAccessListRuleIndex.description: An index value identifying a particular rule within a standard access list. Rules are tested in order of increasing rule index.

ExtAccessListListIndex.name: ExtAccessListListIndex
ExtAccessListListIndex.description: An arbitrary index value identifying an extended access list.

ExtAccessListListIndexOrZero.name: ExtAccessListListIndexOrZero
ExtAccessListListIndexOrZero.description: An arbitrary index value identifying an extended access list or zero for no access list.

ExtAccessListRuleIndex.name: ExtAccessListRuleIndex
ExtAccessListRuleIndex.description: An index value identifying a particular rule within an extended access list. Rules are tested in order of increasing rule index.

RouteAction.name: RouteAction
RouteAction.description: Action to perform on receipt of a packet which matches the destination for a static route. This is one of: - forward the packet to the address specified as the next-hop address - handle the packet locally - reject [drop and send ICMP] - discard [drop but do not send ICMP] - forward the packet using a tunnel.

AdminDistance.name: AdminDistance
AdminDistance.description: The adminstrative distance used in prioritizing routes from different sources when selecting active routes in DC-RTM. The active route is chosen from those available routes which have the lowest associated administrative distance.

InetSubAddressType.name: InetSubAddressType
InetSubAddressType.description: A value that represents a subsequent type of Internet address.

BfdSessionStatus.name: BfdSessionStatus
BfdSessionStatus.description: The current BFD session state of a peer.

IgpShortcutMetricType.name: IgpShortcutMetricType
IgpShortcutMetricType.description: Type of metric value. This is one of: - Absolute, or fixed; the metric value defined is used as a path cost. - Relative; the metric value defined is added to an existing path cost to produce the total cost of a path. Note that, in this case, the metric value defined may be zero, positive or negative.

IfOperStatus.name: IfOperStatus
IfOperStatus.description: The IfOperStatus as defined in RFC 2863.

MjStatus.name: MjStatus
MjStatus.description: The status of a Master Join.

SjStatus.name: SjStatus
SjStatus.description: The status of a Slave Join.

InterfaceScope.name: InterfaceScope
InterfaceScope.description: The scope of an interface or interface user. When components request information about interfaces, the request includes the scope of information that the component wishes to receive. Only interfaces with matching scope are distributed to the component. This is an opaque structure that maps to an ATG_IF_SCOPE_ID. See the definition of ATG_IF_SCOPE_ID for details.
